Eight days after Easter, a priest of our order came from Asumpcion, accompanied by twelve soldiers. This man had been ordered to take upon himself the care of the colony in case he found me dead3 if I was still sick, to act in my stead‚ while I sailed to the city. He was as much rejoiced at my being still alive, asI was at his arriva13 for he dreaded to remain amongst the savages‚ to whom he was unac- customed‚ having till then been always em- ployed as lecturer on philosophy or theology.
